this meander it was easy to image all manner of witches and goblins  lurking
behind trees just beyond my headlamp beam and laughing at  me.  But  it  was
not a bad way to spend Halloween. Eventually I did hit the  trail  and  then
the car at 9:30 PM. 

16 miles, 5000 ft, 10.5  hours,  -  Fay  Pullen,  Kent,
10/31.
