the top and traversed left to the base of a steep open  slope.   This  slope
would be suspect  with  unstable  snow,  but  today  things  were  firm  and
avalanche danger low, so I climbed up and right onto  the  summit  ridge  at
5500 ft.  Here I left the skis and booted up the remaining 600 ft along  the
easy ridge to the summit (3300 ft, 3 hrs).

    I lingered on the summit enjoying the views on this clear sunny day  and
even took the time to sketch a picture of Big Chiwaukum.  I  managed  a  few
good turns in the softening snow of the open slopes  before  the  quick  ski
down the easy road.  The only unpleasantness was the very last bit  carrying
skis back down the patchy snow from the logging road to the car.   

