clearcut  was the worst, blindly following my GPS through head high,
newly frosted brush. Actually the inch long ice crystals were really
beautiful, but I don\'t think I fully appreciated them at the time.
Anyway, I managed to come out right at my car.  Thank heavens for
GPS\'s.  About 7 miles, 3500 ft and 7 hrs - Fay Pullen 12/3/02.
