Welldiggers Ass (5273 ft - 433P - Labyrinth Mtn Quad) - April 12, 2005


Whoever came up with this name?  I agree with John Roper and like  the  name
Yodelin Mtn better. Whatever the name, this mountain makes a pleasant  short
ski trip. I began at the old logging road 3.3 miles E of Stevens Pass,  just
before the highway divides, elevation  3200  ft.   A  small  plowed  pullout
allows parking for 2 or 3 cars.

About Â½ inch of new snow dusted the road at the start.  This grew  to  maybe
3 inches at road end and 4-5 inches on the summit. Weather for the  day  was
alternate snow showers, heavy at times, and sun breaks. The road  is  gentle
enough not to require skins, but it is quite overgrown in places with  small
alder trees. This slowed me down as I wound my way through  and  stopped  to
break off enough branches to help on the downhill run.  A  heavier  snowpack
would cover  more  of  these  obstacles.  I  followed  the  road  through  7
switchbacks to its end at 4800 ft where I put on skins for the  final  steep
climb up an old clear-cut, then woods, topping out directly on  the  summit,
3 miles, 2100 ft and 3 hrs.

For variety, I continued SW along the ridge toward  Pt  5023  descending  to
the saddle then climbing that gentle bump. A nice downhill run back  to  the
saddle and down open clear-cut slopes to intersect  the  road  at  the  last
switchback followed. The road itself could have been twice as fast  but  for
the annoying alders.  I had to keep speed down to avoid getting  tangled  up
in booby traps.

Total: 7.3 miles, 2300 ft and 5:30 hrs.

Fay Pullen


