            'title' => 'Boise Ridge (3080 ft - 420P - Enumclaw Quad) - January 1, 2006',
            'tr' => '

Boise Ridge (3080 ft - 420P - Enumclaw Quad) - January 1, 2006


What better way to start the New Year than to climb a new peak, even  if  it
is a dinky little thing! Sure, I would rather be skiing, but I  had  neither
the time nor the energy. So with half a day and half the energy,  I  settled
for a bike ride. It turned into a very pleasant ride with pleasant  weather.
No rain, not a drop, and even some  sun.   Well  there  was  the  wind  that
almost blew me over, but you can\'t have everything.

I started from the Weyerhaeuser parking lot for  the  Griffin  Russel  Trail
System on Baldy Hill off 410 across from the old mill pond.  Since  I  would
be on private Weyerhaeuser roads, I figured I would have fewer  problems  on
a holiday.  Darned if I didn\'t still run into a truck patrolling  the  road,
but the guy was friendly and didn\'t mind me  biking.  He  said  I  could  go
anywhere I wanted.  However,  he  wasn\'t  Weyerhaeuser,  but  worked  for  a
logging company operating up the  road  and  was  checking  that  all  their
equipment wasn\'t being vandalized.

I followed the mainline road N and turned right at a  major  junction  after
3.2 miles. The gentle grade made for good pedaling until reaching the  final
2-mile spur to the top at 7 miles.  I passed several open gates, one  closed
gate and one downed tree across the road. I parked  the  bike  as  close  as
possible separately to each of the twin summits and hiked the final  100  ft
or so elevation to both.  My conclusion was the S  summit  was  higher,  and
both were a pain of dense trees and rotting  thinned  tree  slash.  But  the
bike ride was a real delight.

Total: 18.8 miles, 2260 ft and 5 hrs.

Fay Pullen

