            'title' => 'Pechugh Pk (5505 ft - 785P - Lester Quad) - January 3, 2006',
            'tr' => '

Pechugh Pk (5505 ft - 785P - Lester Quad) - January 3, 2006


It was back up the Whistler Cr Road (7030), where I was last week, to  climb
this peak across Twin Camp Cr from Sawmill Ridge. This time I  was  able  to
drive up the road to the switchback at 3100 ft,  considerably  farther  than
before. Snowmobiles had recently  been  on  the  road  so  I  had  no  trail
breaking as I stayed on 7030 all the way to the 4720 ft saddle W of  Pechugh
(3.4 miles, 1620 ft, 1:30 hrs). Here I was finally able to  do  my  favorite
thing in the winter world - make fresh tracks in powder snow. I  followed  a
road that switchbacked twice before dead-ending at 5200  ft,  from  where  I
climbed through pleasant open woods at  the  edge  of  a  clear-cut  to  the
forested summit (2400 ft, 2:45 hrs).

I had hoped to ski down from the  summit  through  the  clear-cut,  but  the
small Christmas-sized trees were too dense and the snow cover  too  shallow.
I was, however, able to cut across the lower switchback, although the  turns
were tight.  A couple more feet of snow would make for  a  great  run.  From
the saddle, I decided to climb Pt 5121  to  the  W.   This  peak  lacks  one
contour for 400 feet of prominence. A steep spur dead-ended at 4900  on  the
N slope.  The final climb to the top (2900 ft, 4:10 hrs) through all  manner
of obstacles was made worse by the fact that I had only kicker skins and  my
skis wouldn\'t climb very steeply.

I then unwisely tried to follow the ridge W  to  Colquhoun  Pk  (5173  ft  -
573P). It actually started  out  well  with  a  nice  open  ridge  but  soon
deteriorated to awful dense woods with inadequate snow cover to ski  easily.
I quickly bailed and dropped NW as fast as I could to pick up  the  approach
road and trail up Colquhoun. I have climbed this peak  many  times  on  skis
and it is one of my favorites. I couldn\'t pass up another  ascent  while  so
close (3700 ft, 6 hrs). Fortunately my kicker skins still  stuck  after  the
third application. From the summit it only took an hour to get back  to  the
car.

Total: 12 miles, 3700 ft and 7 hrs

Fay Pullen



