Teanaway Ridge (4943 ft - 303P - Liberty Quad) - January 4, 2006


This turned into a very nice ski tour even though the  start  was  not  that
promising. Despite snowing heavily as I drove over Snoqualmie Pass,  when  I
arrived at the Iron Cr parking lot I found only a scant inch of fresh  stuff
over an icy rain crust created by the high snow level of the  previous  day.
Though not enough for good XC travel  down  low,  it  was  enough  for  good
gliding along the gentle Hovey Cr Road, and by the time I reached the  crest
of the ridge between Hovey Cr and Blue Cr it  had  increased  to  6  inches.
This made for wonderful XC travel along the ridge and over Pt 4217  until  I
intersected the Blue Cr Road  high  up.  This  road,  although  groomed  for
snowmobiles, was not yet tracked for the day and I had  2.5  miles  of  good
gliding to the final short ascent to  the  high  point  of  Teanaway  Ridge.
Rather than retrace my rather long and circuitous up route, I  then  made  a
direct descent down the ridge between Hovey Cr and the  West  Fork  of  Iron
Cr. Although the upper part was steep it was  better  skiing  than  the  map
might indicate. I picked up an old road on the ridge near Pt 4002. The  only
bad part was the short steep bit off the ridge to connect back to the  Hovey
Cr Road, as there was no longer enough fresh snow to cover  the  icy  crust.
Temperatures for the day were in  the  low  20\'s  with  sunbreaks  and  snow
squalls. 10.5 miles, 2700 ft and 7 hrs.

Fay Pullen
