Twin Peaks (5325 ft - P1165 - Lake Philippa Quad) - March 5, 2006


I have wanted to climb Twin Peaks ever since seeing it years ago  from  Goat
Mtn.  But I just never got to it, put off I  suppose,  by  tales  of  horror
from others who had climbed or attempted it.  So when Stefan  came  up  with
this as one of his trips, I jumped at the chance even though things did  not
look all that appealing to start. The weather was not promising,  I  had  my
doubts about Stefan\'s choice of route and way too many people showed up  for
this usually solitary soul. Well, the weather turned out  much  better  than
expected and the route turned out to be downright  pleasant  (you  amaze  me
Stefan with your innovative routes).  But, surprisingly,  the  best  for  me
turned out to be the people.  I think  we  have  the  best  group  of  like-
minded, obsessed, crazy,  interesting,  supportive,  competent  peak-baggers
going.  I enjoyed the company of each and every one of you. It was my  first
trip with Juan, Dave and Grant, but hopefully not my last. It was  great  to
again see Mitch, after a much too long absence, and  Jeff,  Greg,  and  Don,
even after recent trips together. Ian, I admire  your  perseverance.  Stefan
and Paul - this is getting to be a habit, but a good one.  And  Annette,  we
are just getting started.
