Tiptop2 (3276 ft - 636P) & Tiptop3 (3251 ft - 451P) - Tiptop Quad - May 16,
2006


This would have been a very pleasant trip except for the heat.  It was  HOT,
HOT, HOT.  The temperature in Cashmere later in the day was 98 degrees.  And
it didn\'t help that I had things to do at my cabin before starting home  and
ended up hiking in the heat of the day.

From Cashmere, I took the Mission Cr Road. I had no prior knowledge  of  how
to get  up  these  peaks,  counting  on  being  able  to  go  most  anywhere
crosscountry. My first choice was from the NE up  Sherman  Canyon  where  it
looked like I could make a nice loop taking in both tops, but, not being  as
bold as some people I know when it comes to trespassing, I couldn\'t see  any
easy way into the canyon through  private  property  or  past  driveways  to
homes. So I continued S to National Forest land driving  up  Sand  Cr  to  a
small parking spot near Poison Canyon.

An old road-turned-trail followed Poison Cr. This road  was  overgrown  with
brush and worse, nettles, and since I was in shorts my legs  ended  up  full
of scratches and welts. After 0.75 mile a distinct waytrail left the creek  and
climbed steeply up  a  spur  ridge  past  interesting  sandstone  slabs  and
pinnacles. At 2800 ft I began  a  traverse  N  through  gorgeous  fields  of
Arrowleaf Balsamroot below Tiptop2  to  the  saddle  with  Tiptop3.  I  then
followed the ridge, part of which was a delightful  rocky  hogback,  to  the
highpoint of Tiptop3 on the SE end.  Views  were  expansive  and  the  snowy
Enchantments enticing in sharp contrast to my sweltering environment.

I returned to the saddle to follow the ridge S to Tiptop2. A  very  distinct
(horse?) trail led up to this point from the E and presumably the homes  and
ranches along Mission Cr. But I  descending  to  the  S  and  picked  up  my
waytrail leading back to Poison Cr and more encounters with nettles.

I had hoped to climb another top nearby (Tiptop4, 2889 ft)  but  I  was  now
totally wilted and out of liquid refreshment, so I settled for  cooling  off
with a nice dinner at the Big Y CafÃ© and  returning  home  at  a  reasonable
hour.

Total: 4.5 miles, 2600 ft and 4:30 hrs.

Fay Pullen




