            'tr' => '
Dixie Pk (4606 ft - 402P) and Blowdown Mtn (4560+ ft - 240P) - Mt Si Quad -
November 28, 2006

I had thought the heavy lowland snow would make the  timing  just  right  to
ski up the Mt Teneriffe Road. I was wrong. There was barely an inch  at  the
TH, hardly enough to ski on to start.  I had more snow in  my  driveway!  It
defied the logic that the closer you get to  the  mountains  the  more  snow
there is.  Is North Bend in a snow shadow  or  what?  Whatever  the  reason,
there it was and I had to walk 2.5 miles  to  2100ft  before  I  could  start
skiing. But once I hit skiable snow it was all worth it.  What  lovely  snow
it was and what fantastic skiing.  A road led almost to the treed summit  of
Blowdown. The beginning of the ridge from there to  Dixie  was  dense  trees
and not skiable so I descended the road until I could traverse back  to  the
ridge near the saddle.  This was the only hard part.  The rest of the  ridge
to Dixie was open woods and delightful skiing,  except  for  the  last  1/10
mile, which was narrow and rocky. I hiked the final bit to  the  alpine-like
summit and fine views. I had a wonderful ski down the ridge  until  I  could
drop directly to the main road and a fast ski down the road until the  sound
of rocks scraping my bases made me stop and take off  my  skis.   12  miles,
4500 ft, 8 hrs.  Fay Pullen

