            'tr' => '

The Ark (5339 ft - 739P)  - Lake Philippa Quad - February 2, 2007


The Middle Fork Snoqualmie River Road is as potholed  as  ever,  maybe  even
made worse, if that is possible, by rutted snow and ice the last bit to  the
Taylor River TH. It made for very slow driving. The  "trail"  itself,  along
the old road was snow compacted by many footprints and easy traveling.  Most
footprints stayed with the Taylor River, only a few, notably  including  one
set of snowshoe prints, turned left onto the old Quartz  Cr  road  .4  miles
up. The snow was hard enough to make snowshoes unnecessary.  I left mine  in
the car, electing instead to bring only  crampons.  About  2  miles  farther
both Mr. Snowshoe and I took a right onto an even older  road.  Mr  Snowshoe
stuck to the road but I soon grew weary of road plodding and found  it  more
interesting, if not faster, to cut  straight  up  through  the  fairly  open
woods crossing the road twice more. Soon the terrain  steepened  and  became
more open and out came the ice axe and crampons. I  worked  my  way  into  a
