snow warmed sufficiently by the time I left that I didn\'t need crampons  for
the descent. I don\'t know where Mr Snowshoe went but I never saw his  tracks
above where I left the road. For the plod out  the  road  I  was  pleasantly
distracted by an almost  constant  view  of  the  impressive  cliffs  of  Mt
Garfield.

