            'title' => 'Pk 4534 (574P - Baring Quad) and Pk 4494 (774P - Evergreen Mtn Quad) - April 7, 2007',
            'tr' => '
Pk 4534 (574P - Baring Quad) and Pk 4494 (774P - Evergreen Mtn Quad) -
April 7, 2007

These are two peaks I had my eye on but didn\'t have time for  when  I  skied
up Flapjack Point a couple of weeks ago. This  time  I  was  able  to  drive
about a mile farther up Eagle Cr Road (6514) to 2100 ft. Another .3 mile  of
walking brought me to enough consistent snow  for  skiing.  I  followed  the
road for 3 miles to where I could easily leave it to climb up  onto  the  SE
ridge of Pk 4534. Although much of the ridge was in forest it  was  pleasant
skiing and there were many fantastic views of Baring, Merchant and  Townsend
along the way. An open spot just before the wooded true summit  made  for  a
lovely lunch break (4.5 miles, 2400 ft, 3 hrs).

For the return I stayed high on the ridge, going over a 3960  ft  knoll  for
more good views, and made a long horseshoe traverse, quite steep in  places,
around a side valley of Eagle Creek until I  could  climb  up  onto  the  NW
ridge of Pk 4494. I then followed this  wooded  ridge  to  the  summit  (9.6
miles, 3900 ft, 6 hrs). I picked up a road on  the  other  side,  cutting  a
switchback through a clearcut with excellent skiing, and  followed  it  back
to the main road to close my loop trip.

I highly recommend this area for ski touring. It doesn\'t seem to be  heavily
used (although I did see evidence of some snowmobile use),  the  terrain  is
friendly for skiing with multiple destinations possible and in good  weather
the views are fantastic.

Total: 13.8 miles, 3900 ft and 8 hrs.

Fay Pullen


