Silver Eagle Pk (aka Bald Eagle Pk) - 6259 ft - 1019P - Big Snow Mtn Quad -
May 17, 2007


I am not sure what to call this peak. Beckey calls  it  Bald  Eagle.  Jeff\'s
Master List calls it Silver Eagle. The map calls the 6241 ft  peak  next  to
it Bald Eagle, as does Jeff while Beckey calls that one Silver Eagle. It  is
all too confusing for me. I am going with Jeff. You may call the  peak  what
you wish.  Whatever the name, I had this peak on my list  ever  since  doing
the companion 6241 ft one with Mitch in 2003.  Oh, and it is  a  Home  Court
Peak.

I started at 8:20 from just across the bridge over the  E  Fork  Foss  River
and headed uphill through open woods to the N ridge.  I  then  followed  the
ridge most of the way. It was easy going to start with little or  no  brush.
I began running into snow about 4000 ft and it became  consistent  somewhere
about 4500. For the most part I stayed right on the nose of the  ridge  with
very little variation. I passed a rock  step  at  about  4600  ft  and  then
increasingly deep slushy unreliable snow on the narrow corniced  ridge  made
travel slower and more difficult. I stuck with the ridge to  about  5200  ft
where I was forced to descend to the left (E) to avoid  cliffs.  Steep  snow
led back to the ridge above the cliffs. There was  one  final  narrow  rocky
section passed on the right (W) before the summit. I started in fog  but  by
the time I made the summit at 2:45 the sun had appeared and  glorious  views
of the Alpine Lakes with it. I spent a good hour  on  top  enjoying  it  and
them. I found a film can register left by Fred Beavon in August,  2006.  All
in all a very nice scramble but harder and longer than expected due to  snow
conditions. At least I did get down before dark (7:40).

Total: 6 miles, 5100 ft and 11:20 hrs.

Fay Pullen
