            'tr' => '

Birthday Climbs


By a strange coincidence both Ian and my son Walter have the same  birthday,
November 19. Of course the birth year is a bit different, by some 25  years.
I was able to celebrate both birthdays, the day before with  Ian  and  gang,
the day of with Walter.

Sexagenarian Pk (aka Higgins W Pk - 4880+ ft - 440P -  Mt  Higgins  Quad)  -
November 18, 2007

In keeping with celebrating Ian\'s 60th birthday, John  Roper  came  up  with
this previously unnamed peak as an appropriate goal and the  nearby  Higgins
Lookout site as an alternate for those less inclined  to  peakbagging.  With
dual attractive destinations, shared organization  by  John  and  Mitch  and
much better than expected weather, 19 humans and 3 dogs showed  up  for  the
festivities.  I  am  sure  the  2  fellows  unattached  to  our  group   who
encountered this mass of celebrants on the lookout site  didn\'t  quite  know
what to make of it all. After popping the champagne cork and  congratulating
Ian, the majority of people started back down  the  trail,  while  4  of  us
(Dick Kegel, Jim Nelson, Ian and I) set out  for  Sexagenarian.  I  am  sure
more would have joined, but the peak  looked  rather  frightful  and  cliffy
from the lookout, and though there was not that much snow what little  there
was, was very icy. We traversed past cliffs to the W  side  and  worked  our
way  up  steep  brushy  and  forested  dirt  made  treacherous  by  the  icy
conditions. Crampons would have been helpful. It all took maybe  45  minutes
from the lookout. Coming down was even longer as we used  my  60  ft  "panic
rope" in a series of short arm rappels to avoid  slipping  on  the  ice.  We
were all happy to have this assist in the slicker spots, with  the  possible
excerption of Dick. He soon found it too much of a bother and just took  off
downhill. I was very impressed. With better conditions none  of  this  would
have been a problem at all. I had never climbed  with  either  Dick  or  Jim
before, and Ian is always a pleasure, so this little diversion was a  lovely
finale to a fun day.

9.5 miles, 4100 ft and 7:45 hrs

Fools Day Pk (5203 ft - 403P - Kachess Lk Quad) - November 19, 2007

I was out again the next day on my son\'s birthday. It  was  a  challenge  to
find something neither of us had done, close enough  and  accessible  enough
that it could be fit into a short
day as he had to be home in time to finish celebrating with his new wife.  I
came up with this little peak near Thorp Mtn. I had thought  to  go  up  the
old road on the N side but we couldn\'t drive that far due to a  snowy  road.
We ran into much more new snow in this area than I  had  encountered  on  Mt
Higgins and after slipping and sliding in some 5-6 inches of  the  stuff,  I
opted for Plan B, a XC route up  the  E  ridge.  This  was  really  quite  a
pleasant route with little brush and in 2 hours we were on top. In  fact  it
was so pleasant that I am keeping it in mind as a future ski  trip.  With  a
foot more snow it would be very skiable indeed although then one would  have
to start from the Cle Elum River.

2.5 miles, 2000 ft and 3:30 hrs
Fay Pullen


