February 12. 2008

Stefan and I had scoped out the first 2 of these peaks after climbing  Kiona
3 (also 1840+ ft) and Randle 3 (1808 ft) in December but  ran  out  of  time
and incentive to crash wet brush. We were able to drive the quarry  road  to
the east side of Kiona 2 but I unexpectedly  found  this  road  gated  shut.
Instead I parked on Bowen Road on the west side a short  distance  from  Hwy
12 and went up pleasant woods at the edge  of  the  clear-cut  clearly  seen
from below. I hit a logging road on the ridge, coming from the south,  which
I followed to a cat track that went to the summit. Some  snow.   1.1  miles,
840 ft 1:14 hrs RT.

