Long Hill (1480+ ft - 500P - Enumclaw Quad) - February 25, 2008

Thanks to Stefan, Paul and I climbed Long Hill this afternoon. His  proposed
route avoiding the Big Bad Gate worked like a charm. We met along Ryan Rd  a
little after 4 pm, Paul found a place to park his  car  lower  down,  and  I
drove mine to park in a wide spot just past the switchback. We  ducked  into
the woods at a convenient spot and worked our way downhill until  hitting  a
very muddy old road. This led to the road  going  to  the  reservoirs  which
then led to the main road from the Big Bad Gate. From this  intersection  we
essentially went straight uphill to the top. Some minor  brush  but  overall
not bad travel. The summit high point was at the far end of the  ridge.   We
started hiking at 4:30 and reached the top at 5:30.  Since  it  was  getting
dark on the way down and we didn\'t want to lose out way on the direct  route
back  to  the  car,  we  elected  to  follow  the  reservoir  road  out.  We
encountered the worse brush with stickers descending from the  reservoir  to
Ryan Road. Thankfully it was very short. We came out  just  inside  the  Big
Bad Gate and  both  took  enormous  pleasure  in  ducking  under  it  -  the
highlight of the day. We finished the trip  with  a  1.5  miles  walk  along
roads back to the car.

Total: 3.5 miles, 950 ft and 2:10 hrs.

|                                                                          |


                                 Top of Form


