            'tr' => '
Mitchell Hill (1300+ ft - 380P - Fall City Quad) - February 26, 2008

Now I don\'t want any comments about how there  is  a  much  shorter  way  up
Mitchell Hill from Preston on the south where you can almost  drive  to  the
top (this means you Paul - besides, you do know I  like  to  do  things  the
hard way). I know the usual goal for blobs is to find the shortest,  fastest
way up, but this route turned out to be so pleasant  and  enjoyable  that  I
can\'t help but recommend it. It is all  on  quiet  semi-forested  DNR  lands
with good hiking (or possibly biking) roads and  trails  and  absolutely  no
trespass issues. It would make a great dog walk trip.

I began at a gated DNR logging road off SE Issaquah Fall City  Road  at  240
ft. The road climbed steadily to a minor  ridge,  dropped  100  ft  off  the
other side to cross a creek and climbed once again to end at 1000 feet at  a
large pile of charred logs where there were nice  views  of  the  Snoqualmie
River Valley and snow capped North Fork  peaks.  Here  I  met  a  fellow  on
horseback training an impatient filly. We chatted  while  the  filly  danced
around anxious to get back to the barn. From here  a  trail  connected  with
another road that I took  uphill  past  a  small  (cell?)  tower.  The  road
continued but I soon left it to follow a shortcut trail  through  the  woods
to yet another (or maybe the same) road higher up that went  to  just  below
the wooded high point. This entire route goes through  no  private  property
or past no houses, but I did set off two dogs barking at a home  just  below
the top on the south side.

This finally finishes off the Fall City Quad for me.

Total: 5.75 miles, 1380 ft and 2:30 hrs.

Fay

