            'tr' => '
Mazama Ridge (5680+ ft), McClure Rock (7360+ ft) and Panorama Point (6920+
ft) - Mt Rainier East Quad - March 6, 2008

I returned to Paradise two days after my foggy Mildred Point  trip  for  the
views I had missed. I wasn\'t going to bother sending out a  TR  but  then  I
couldn\'t resist sharing the photos.  Nothing new here but I  never  tire  of
the beauty of Mt Rainier (when you can actually see it) even if it is in  my
back yard. I combined these three points of interest to make  a  fun  mellow
loop and took my time enjoying  it.  The  fresh  snow  was  melting  in  the
morning sun and preserved in the shade making for generally good  skiing.  I
never used skins the entire trip but did need my ski  crampons  on  a  short
steep icy windblown section below McClure Rock. The ski off  Panorama  Point
was challenging for me in my light gear  as  the  snow  began  to  ice  over
quickly under afternoon clouds. The rest of the way down was delightful.

Due to construction on the new visitor center (Yes  Jim,  it  is  there  and
this time I did notice it), during the week that area is closed and  parking
is limited to the old visitor center.

8.5 miles, 2500 ft and 5:30 hrs.

Fay

