            'tr' => '
Cowap Pk (5658 ft - 858P), East Canyon Ridge  (5408  ft  -  408P)  &  Middle
Canyon Ridge (5405 ft - 405P) - Bearpaw Mtn  Quad;  and  West  Canyon  Ridge
(5327 ft - 687P) - Glacier Quad - September 17-18, 2008

Day 1: Cowap and East & Middle Canyon Ridge - I used the last  of  the  good
weather spell to hike this mellow pleasant ridge ramble. I  began  from  the
Damfino Lake TH which is some 15 miles up Road 31 (Canyon Cr Road)  off  the
Mt Baker Highway. I followed the Damfino Lake Trail .7 miles to  the  Canyon
Ridge Trail junction and this .4 miles farther to the  Boundary  Way  Trail.
This trail can be followed to the NE ridge for a walkup route but I chose  a
shorter faster route directly up  a steep gully that hit the ridge  just  SW
of the summit and involved a  short  scramble.  From  the  summit  I  had  a
splendid though somewhat hazy view of American Border peak where I had  just
been a few days before (1450 ft, 1:30 ht).

