            'tr' => '
Round Mtn (5970 ft - 650P) and Twin Peaks (5920+ ft - 440P) -  Spiral  Butte
Quad - February 28, 2009

Back to back wonderful ski trips. I risk getting spoiled. I  did  this  tour
the day after Goat Mtn. Normally I like a day or two  to  recover  but  when
the snow is this good you have to take  advantage  of  it  while  it  lasts,
which often isn\'t long. Even one day can make a big difference.  Stefan  was
gracious enough to allow me to accompany him on his outing to White Pass  at
the last minute when I saw what he had planned could be  done  on  skis.  It
was a little more challenging than Goat but still very skiable.  Stefan,  of
course, was on snowshoes. We climbed up alongside the ski run to the  ridge.
At that point we left the hordes behind and saw no one else.   Stefan  stuck
to the ridge line the whole  way  going  up  and  over  two  bumps  while  I
contoured around both through delightful woods  before  gaining  the  ridge.
Even with his added elevation  gain  Stefan  went  faster  that  I  did.  No
surprise there. The 18" of fresh powder made for excellent skiing. Only  the
steep narrow section of Twin Peaks west ridge before it leveled  off  and  a
short bare spot where I had to remove skis  presented  any  difficulties  at
all. The run down to the Round saddle was to die for. I could do  no  wrong.
Mostly we both did our own  thing,  meeting  on  the  summits,  with  Stefan
always ahead. The only time I beat him was on the return run  down  the  ski
area.

Total: 8 miles, 3000 ft and 6:30 hrs

Fay Pullen

