            'tr' => '
Mt Higgins Quad 2 (3775 ft - 495P - Mt Higgins Quad) - March 29, 2009

More new snow and high avalanche danger once again kept me to a low peak.  I
had originally planned to ski up McGillicuddys Pk (4200+ ft). It had  looked
so simple on the map which showed roads going  all  the  way  to  top.  Even
Stefan\'s report from January 2007 indicated it was doable. But I knew I  was
in trouble when I reached the Mt Higgins TH.  The  road  was  abandoned  and
ditched right from the start and partially overgrown, the latter made  worse
by about 3 inches of fresh snow  that  caused  branches  to  bend  over  the
meager path and then drench me as I forced my through.  I  kept  hoping  the
road would get better. It didn\'t. Finally at the crossing of Rollins  Cr  (a
50 ft deep trench with no sign of the make ship bridge mentioned by  Stefan)
and with no prospect of making my  destination,  I  gave  up  on  the  road.
Seeking to salvage the  day,  I  forced  a  way  straight  uphill.  After  a
horrible steep section of tight trees, I emerged onto the plateau  north  of
Higgins2 where I found a series of better old roads and  more  open  terrain
leading nicely  to  that  summit.  There  were  even  a  few  limited  views
highlighted by  an  unfamiliar  attractive  low  peak  to  the  NW  I  later
identified as Big Deer. I skied down the Higgins2  road  as  no  way  was  I
returning the way I had come. I was  worried  how  this  would  be,  but  it
turned into a very nice continuous run down that road which was etched  into
the steep open hillside.

Total: 7 miles, 2500, and 7:30 hrs.

Fay Pullen



