I was hard-pressed to find anywhere to  go  on  Wednesday  where  it  wasn\'t
raining.  Since all I really wanted to do  was  stretch  leg  muscles  still
sore from Stefan\'s Grasshopper climb and since I had always wanted to  check
out the Durr Road route to the North  Yakima  Rim  Trail,  this  seemed  the
perfect time to give that a try. Oh but the weather  was  nasty.  It  rained
heavily the whole way to Ellensburg though improved  a  bit  once  there.  I
found Durr Road to  be  quite  drivable  and  the  ford  across  Umtanum  Cr
manageable. Once on the ridge itself  vehicles  were  still  allowed,  so  I
drove the rough 4X4 roads in each direction as far as  I  felt  comfortable.
I wanted to get to the high point of Umtanum Ridge to the  west  and  (as  a
bonus) to Wenas BM to the east.  The farther one  got  from  Durr  Road  the
worse the roads became and in some places were quite  rough  and  muddy.  It
was raining lightly but very windy for both hikes. At least it  seemed  like
light rain. It must have rained harder than I thought  because  as  I  drove
down Durr Road at the end of the day I hit a section that  had  turned  into
gumbo mud that completely clogged my tires giving  me  zero  traction.  Much
worse than anything on the 4X4 roads up top.  I  slip-slided  down,  inching
along in low-low gear at 1 mph until I hit better  gravel.  Scary!  It  sure
wasn\'t that bad going up.

Umtanum Ridge: 6.5 miles, 1300 ft and 2:45 hr

Wenas BM: 1.6 miles, 405 ft and: 45 hr

Fay

No pictures, it was too foggy.

