            'tr' => '
Pickhandle Point (6361 ft) and Crown Point (6480+ ft) Ski Tour - Norse  Peak
Quad - April 16, 2009

I wanted some quality skiing close to home and this tour  fit  the  bill.  I
also explored some new territory.  I have skied  up  Pickhandle  Point  many
times but never from Pickhandle Gap,  only  from  Bear  Gap  and  Pickhandle
Ridge.

Starting from Lot C, I followed the cat tracks to the top of the Gold  Hills
Lift (closed for the season). From here it is best to pass  the  steep  step
into Pickhandle Basin through open woods right  of  the  draining  gully.  I
like this whole area as its sees little traffic and I usually  have  it  all
to myself. Most backcountry skiers go to  either  Silver  Basin  or  Bullion
Basin. From Pickhandle Gap I traversed lovely terrain, though  a  tad  steep
at the top, to Pickhandle Point and lunch. The day was young, the snow  good
and the terrain called me on to Gold Hill Ridge, where I had never  been.  I
returned over Crown Point  for  a  very  pleasant  loop.  Snow  varied  from
preserved powder in protected areas to a couple inches of melting  slush  in
the sun but both made for very good skiing. I  was  down  before  the  slush
froze to breakable crust.

Total: 8 miles, 3300 ft and 7 hours

Fay Pullen



