            'tr' => '
Bald Mtn (5481 ft - P1241 - Glacier Quad) - January 3, 2010

Bald Mtn is an impressive rocky  little  peak  directly  north  of  Glacier.
Stefan planned to climb  this  peak  on  this  same  day  but  was  starting
directly from Hwy 542 at the low elevation of 800  ft.  Since  the  snowline
was still quite high that meant walking bare  logging  roads  for  miles.  I
declined to join him as I  really  wanted  to  ski  and  not  hike.  Then  I
discovered the night before that I could drive to 3400 ft via the Canyon  Cr
road which would get me to snow and close enough for a day ski  trip.  So  I
knew Stefan would be on the peak but he didn\'t know I would be. What a  kick
it would be if we met on the summit.

Although I could drive close enough to get near  the  peak  I  still  wasn\'t
sure I could climb it on skis as the final 800 ft or so are quite steep  and
rocky. It turned out to be a delightful ski trip and I was able to  get  all
the way to the summit on skis. I began at 3400 ft on road 3140. The  driving
was not too bad although icy in spots and I stopped before  it  became  more
so. The hard core 4X4ers had only gotten a quarter mile or so  father  so  I
didn\'t do too badly. From there a lone snowmobile track took over.  Although
a designated snowmobile route this road doesn\'t seem to be overly  used  and
none came up on this Sunday. Maybe there isn\'t enough snow yet.

Starting at 9:30, I skied the road  about  3  miles,  rapidly  getting  into
fresh snow, to an untracked spur heading toward Bald Lake. This was kind  of
out of my way. I had hoped to take a short cut directly to the lake but  old
roads shown on the map were now nonexistent and the terrain  was  too  steep
and dense for XC travel. I had to stick to the main roads.  The  spur  ended
in a clear-cut not too far from the lake but it was still an effort to  find
a way XC. Once at the lake the terrain opened up and the skiing  was  great.
I skirted the lake, traversed under cliffs and made my way to  a  5000  foot
saddle. On the other side was a lovely basin beneath the cliffs of the  west
face of Bald. Here was the crux. I had to get past  these  cliffs.  As  luck
would have it an open slope led to the west ridge. It was quite  steep  near
the top but doable on skis.

Just as I topped the steep slope onto the west ridge who should I  run  into
but Stefan and Greg coming down. What timing. One more minute  and  I  would
have missed them completely. I think I really surprised them. It  was  great
fun seeing them. The rest of the way  to  the  summit  was  along  a  gentle
ridge. I ate lunch while enjoying  a  panorama  view  on  a  day  where  the
weather turned out much better than expected. I then ended with a  wonderful
ski down reaching the car while it was still daylight.

Total: 9 miles, 2600 ft and 7 hrs

Fay Pullen

