            'tr' => '
Hogback Mtn (6789 ft - P1989) and Hogback Ridge  (6652  ft  -  P132)  -  Old
Snowy Quad - March 3, 2010

The expansion of White Pass into Hogback Basin is taking place next  season,
so I wanted to get back into that area one  more  time  before  it  will  no
longer be the exclusive domain of backcountry  skiers.  There  were  several
inches of new snow  which  made  for  generally  good  conditions.  The  day
started sunny and warm but soon clouded up ending with  snow  showers,  some
of which were quite heavy.

After checking out the whimsical Snow Castle near the Day Lodge, I skied  up
the Main Street run to the base of Chair 4. Starting shortly  after  opening
downhill traffic was very light. From the chair base I skied  into  pleasant
untracked woods but soon ran into evidence of the expansion. The towers  for
two new lifts are already in place as are the cuts for  new  runs.  However,
once on Hogback Mtn (2400 ft, 2:45) I left  all  that  behind.  I  continued
along the gentle, but corniced ridge intending to go as far as  possible.  I
didn\'t count on a rocky pinnacle blocking the way. There  is  no  indication
of such an obstacle on the map. This forced me off the ridge into the  basin
to the E and onto a saddle above Shoe Lake. From here an easy  traverse  and
short climb led to Pt 6652 (2900 ft, 4 hrs) where I had a pleasant lunch  in
the sun.

Not wanting to quit yet I skied S and E off Pt 6652. Snow in  the  open  was
melting in the sun and getting heavy but once I hit the protected forest  it
was powder and the skiing very good. I kept going all  the  way  to  a  flat
meadow below Hidden Spring at 5400 ft where I decided it was  time  to  turn
around at 3:00. Of course now I had to  regain  the  1200  ft  back  to  the
saddle above Shoe Lake. At this point it began to  snow  rather  heavily.  I
removed skins again for a nice ski into the basin below the pinnacle  but  I
chose a low traverse back to Hogback Basin and  was  able  make  it  without
skinning up again. I skied the new runs and Main  Street  down  to  the  car
reaching it just at dark (6:30). Since the ski area was now closed I had  no
traffic to dodge. It snowed lightly all the way down.

Total: 13 miles, 4300 ft and 9:30 hrs

Fay Pullen

