Good grief! Winter  storm  warnings!  Avalanche  warnings!  Washington  Pass
closed temporarily! Is this really  May?  Our  reversed  spring-winter  just
keeps on coming. What to do? I needed a safe destination to ski and  decided
on this trip. I have had it in mind for a while but in a strange  twist  was
not able to do it this winter as there was  never  enough  lowland  snow  to
ski. The conditions were perfect today and it ended up being a  surprisingly
enjoyable tour.

I drove 20.7 miles from Darrington on FRs 2810, 2811 and 28.  It  took  over
an hour to drive this distance due  to  many  potholes  and  much  new  snow
starting at about 2000 ft. I pushed it as far as I  could  in  my  jeep  but
finally came to a dead stop at 3200 ft. No other vehicles had  been  up  the
road or came later. Snow was over a foot deep, wet and  heavy,  and  it  was
snowing when I started but the weather improved as the day went on.

Lucky Logger - I took a spur road right to a clear-cut on  the  SW  side.  I
was afraid I would have to crash tight trees but once out of  the  clear-cut
the woods were open and  pleasant  for  skiing.  No  views  on  this  wooded
summit. I skied more open woods NW to intersect the main road (28) again.

Ole Mtn - This peak has two summits  of  equal  contours.  I  couldn\'t  tell
which was higher. Both have been clear-cut with a spur road to the  top  and
nice views. The ridge to Ole 2 was especially delightful.

Slash Mtn - This peak deserves a better name than this derogatory one as  it
