            'tr' => '
Tatoosh Lakes Quad1 (5880+ ft - P520 - Tatoosh Lakes Quad) - June 3, 2010

I originally didn\'t think I would bother writing a TR for this peak  in  the
Tatoosh Wilderness as I expected it to be  an  unpleasant  brush  bash  that
would interest few people. However, it turned out to be  such  an  enjoyable
and easy little climb I just had to  pass  it  on.  And  the  views  of  the
backside of the Tatoosh Range from the summit are quite stunning.  The  only
real problem is the access road (5260) leaving Skate Cr  Rd  52  at  Johnson
Cr. I was able to drive it 4 miles to the switchback at 3560 ft (stopped  by
snow here) in my Jeep but parts of it are  very  rough  with  several  creek
fords, near washouts and much water damage. The last  mile  is  particularly
rutted and bad. A few more heavy  rain  storms  and  it  may  no  longer  be
passable.

From the switchback I hiked the road .4 mile to a spur just before a  creek.
I tried following this spur but it is so overgrown it is of no help  and  it
is best to just go uphill alongside the creek. The  first  part  was  a  bit
brushy until leaving the second growth  but  it  was  short.  Then  pleasant
brushless forest in the wilderness was easily ascended to an open  basin  at
4600 ft. Snow was solid in the woods. The basin showed  evidence  of  recent
climax avalanches all the way down to dirt. Goat trails led through a  short
bare cliffy section to an upper snow  basin  and  the  SE  ridge  which  was
followed over the false summit to the  true  summit.  The  higher  snow  was
still soft and slushy but snowshoes were not needed (nor taken).

Total: 4 miles and 2700 ft RT. 3 hours up, 1:25 hours down  and  a  glorious
hour on the summit basking in the sun.

Fay

Oh, does anyone have a name for this peak? It certainly deserves one. I  did
build a cairn and leave a register (but not a name).

