I climbed N first. Some annoying snowbrush and small downed  trees.  An  old
road winds its way up E side and I crossed it twice but probably  easier  to
just go uphill. 500 ft and 37 minutes RT.

Back to car for  M.  Followed  road  and  dropped  to  saddle.  Fence  here.
Traversed around 4041 on way there. (Went over it on way back.)  Dropped  to
next saddle. Fairly good roads intersect at the fence here. May be  able  to
drive to this point. Not sure where to pick  up  these  roads  but  probably
from Newby Cr. Easily follow along fence on path  to  top.  Must  cross  the
fence to Access summit. 1000 ft and 1:30 RT.

