anyway. I caught only glimpses of Bald and  Black.  Besides  I  love  making
tracks in fresh snow. The final spur started  overgrown  but  improved  near
the top. The summit was in dense forest slightly off the  spur  and  someone
had marked it with flagging hanging off a tree branch  (Stefan?).   The  run
down was very pleasant although the last mile was thin, slushy  and  in  the
rain. As expected when I reached the car the gate was closed.

