thin to start but again got better higher. The road has several  quite  long
level sections below the Josephine-Napoleon Saddle but steepens above.  From
the saddle on as I entered a more northerly exposure the snow was very  nice
with fresh on both the road and trees.  From there it was another 2.5  miles
to Josephine. The road went all the way to the  top.  I  had  expected  some
nice views as the forecast was sunny and indeed it  had  started  that  way.
But something happened on my way up and by the time I  reached  the  top  it
