"Skate-Berry Pk" (4880+ ft - P600 ft - Waypenayo Pk Quad) - April 22, 2011

This peak between Berry and Skate Creeks south of Ashford is a  long  mostly
road ski. It was almost too long for a day trip but I needed something  long
and mindless after being out of town on personal business for  well  over  a
week. Mountains and exercise always help me put things in perspective.

I did follow the weather while I was gone and so was aware  that  conditions
had continued cool and wet. Still I was astonished  that  I  couldn\'t  drive
farther than a mile on Big Creek Road 84 to 2200 ft.  I  had  hoped  to  get
much farther. Will winter ever end? Oh well I did say I wanted a  long  trip
didn\'t I? Skiing was quite pleasant on the gentle road with  the  snow  firm
and well packed from old snowmobile  tracks.  None  of  the  machines  today
though. I stayed left at the junction with 8440 to Towhead Gap at  6  miles,
dropped slightly to cross Berry Creek, and then climbed  again  to  a  minor
spur 1.75 miles farther. The day was sunny and warm with  many  varied  views
of Mt Rainier.

The rough spur ended in a clear-cut where I soon entered trees with  limited
views. The last 900 ft from the end of the spur was slow going  in  the  now
wet unconsolidated snow. I removed  skis  and  kicked  steps  up  the  final
steepish 300 feet to the wooded summit arriving at 4:00 (10 miles, 2900  ft,
6 hrs).

The return trip took 3.5 hours, helped on the lower flat road  by  the  fact
that it was in the shade and icing over which speeded things up and  allowed
me to make the car well before dark.

Total: 20 miles, 3000 ft and 9:30 hrs

Fay Pullen

